The Ministry of Tourism might give guarantees to hoteliers to help them get long-term funds to refurbish and upgrade their facilities, Principal Secretary Fatima Mohamed has said.Speaking in Kilifi, she said most tourist attraction sites are old, some having been built in 1980s and 1990s. Mohamed said some operate below international standards and deliver substandard services. I appeal to tourism investors to upgrade their tourist sites," she said. Hotels should encourage domestic tourism, and the ministry is willing to help design products, and the Kenya Tourism Board shall market them."Accommodation and food service sector grew by 15.3 per cent in the April-June period compared to a decline of 5.0 per cent in the same quarter of 2015.